genresAdvancedInfo.name: norwegian house
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Norwegian house is a subgenre of electronic dance music that originated in Norway. It is characterized by its upbeat tempo, repetitive beats, and use of synthesizers and other electronic instruments. Norwegian house music often features catchy melodies and uplifting lyrics, and it is popular in clubs and festivals around the world. Many Norwegian house music producers have achieved global success, including Kygo and Alan Walker.
